<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Napoli president Aurelio De Laurentiis has tested positive for coronavirus after reportedly attending a meeting with 20 represetantives from Serie A clubs. </p>

<p>On Wednesday reports from Italian media claimed an individual from the assembly had been diagnosed with COVID-19, with the news possibly causing a 'domino effect' and requiring all those who attended to have tests and go into self-isolation.</p>

<p>It comes as a huge blow to Napoli and the Italian top flight with the new Serie A season just over a week away.</p>

<p>Napoli's president Aurelio De Laurentiis has tested positive for COVID-19, the club confirmed </p>

<p>A brief statement on Napoli's official website read: 'SSC Napoli announces that President Aurelio De Laurentiis tested positive for Covid-19 following the swab carried out yesterday.'</p>

<p>Italian outlet La Repubblica previously claimed that one of the directors or chairman at the meeting had tested positive and was not wearing their mask correctly.</p>

<p>Club chiefs were meeting in person for the first time in months, after being forced to speak virtually when lockdown began in Italy, to discuss preparations for the 2020-21 campaign. </p>

<p>It comes as a blow to Napoli with the new 2020-21 Serie A campaign just over a week away </p>

<p>De Laurentiis has reportedly suffered with pneumonia recently and his diagnosis could have a big impact on the way the club conducts transfer business.</p>

<p>Napoli have sold midfielder Allan to Everton for £25m this summer and have brought in Victor Osimhen for £74m as their only addition so far.</p>

<p>The Naples outfit face an away trip to Parma in the first Serie A game of the season on September 20. </p>
